propertyDescriptor.name: File Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The size of the file that will be used

propertyDescriptor.name: Batch Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The number of FlowFiles to be transferred in each invocation

propertyDescriptor.name: Data Format
propertyDescriptor.description: Specifies whether the data should be Text or Binary

propertyDescriptor.name: Unique FlowFiles
propertyDescriptor.description: If true, each FlowFile that is generated will be unique. If false, a random value will be generated and all FlowFiles will get the same content but this offers much higher throughput

propertyDescriptor.name: generate-ff-custom-text
propertyDescriptor.description: If Data Format is text and if Unique FlowFiles is false, then this custom text will be used as content of the generated FlowFiles and the File Size will be ignored. Finally, if Expression Language is used, evaluation will be performed only once per batch of generated FlowFiles

propertyDescriptor.name: character-set
propertyDescriptor.description: Specifies the character set to use when writing the bytes of Custom Text to a flow file.

propertyDescriptor.name: Delete Attributes Expression
propertyDescriptor.description: Regular expression for attributes to be deleted from FlowFiles.  Existing attributes that match will be deleted regardless of whether they are updated by this processor.

properties.nameKey: NiFi Flow-Update flow parameters-Delete Attributes Expression

propertyDescriptor.name: Store State
propertyDescriptor.description: Select whether or not state will be stored. Selecting 'Stateless' will offer the default functionality of purely updating the attributes on a FlowFile in a stateless manner. Selecting a stateful option will not only store the attributes on the FlowFile but also in the Processors state. See the 'Stateful Usage' topic of the 'Additional Details' section of this processor's documentation for more information

propertyDescriptor.name: Stateful Variables Initial Value
propertyDescriptor.description: If using state to set/reference variables then this value is used to set the initial value of the stateful variable. This will only be used in the @OnScheduled method when state does not contain a value for the variable. This is required if running statefully but can be empty if needed.

properties.nameKey: NiFi Flow-Update flow parameters-Stateful Variables Initial Value
